Refractory ascites and dilutional hyponatremia: current management and new aquaretics. Ascites is the most common complication of cirrhosis and is associated with 50% mortality at 2 years if patients do not receive orthotopic liver transplantation. Recently the International Ascites Club defined ascites into three groups: In grade I ascites fluid is detected only by ultrasound in grade II, ascites is moderate with symmetrical distention of the abdomen